<TITLE> RAB arrests 4 on murder charge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion arrested a man and three of his associates for killing Wahiduzzaman Ramiz, a BCL activist. Saiful Islam Kajal, 21, arrested Tuesday night, confessed of being involved in the killing when he was produced in front of journalists at RAB-2 office on Wednesday noon. Lt Col Ali Reza Khandakar, head of RAB-2 told journalists that they had arrested Kajal, one of the killers and three others, Shahidul Islam Shwapan, 21, Maruf Amin, 18 and Al-Mamun Ronny, 18, from road 7 of Adabar Shekhertek on Tuesday at around 8pm. He said that Ramiz was killed over a garment business dispute. They have been trying to arrest the main planner of the murder. Kajal said that Akram, the top criminal of Nabi group gave them arms to kill Ramiz. RAB managed to arrest only Kajal, who was one of the three-man killing squad. Wahiduzzaman Ramiz, a BCL activist of road no 12 of Adabar Shekhertek, was killed on April 13. 
